description.plain:
Mabel McVey, known simply as Mabel, is a singer and songwriter based in London, United Kingdom.

Born in Malaga, Spain and raised in Stockholm, Sweden, she is the daughter of singer and songwriter Neneh Cherry and Massive Attack producer Cameron McVey. She began her music career in 2015 with her debut single, “Know Me Better.” Follow-up singles included “My Boy My Town” and “Thinking of You.” In May 2017, she released the 4-track Bedroom EP featuring the title track and her breakout single, “Finders Keepers.” After releasing a mixtape, Ivy to Roses, in October that year, she started 2018 with the release of her single “Fine Line.” The track and follow-up singles, “Ring Ring” (with Jax Jones and Rich the Kid) and “One Shot,” were added to a revised version of the mixtape in January 2019, which also included her first UK top 3 single, “Don’t Call Me Up.” The latter single featured on her long-awaited debut album, High Expectations, released on August 2, which also included the UK top 10 single “Mad Love.”

songs.title: Don’t Call Me Up

description.plain: “Don’t Call Me Up” is all about getting over your exes. In the beginning of the song, Mabel talks about her ex ruining the time out with her friends and by the end of the song she has completely cut off her ex. She doesn’t want anything to do with her ex because she is doing better without him.

songs.full_title: Finders Keepers by Mabel (Ft. Kojo Funds)
songs.title: Finders Keepers

description.plain: In this song, Mabel is addressing a potential hookup (likely in a club). She is making the case that they should just act now and not overthink anything because they’ve found each other in that moment and that is enough. Throughout the song, she urges her interest to put their arms around her and basically just go for it – she isn’t asking for anything serious or defined –  just a physical connection in that moment.

songs.full_title: Boyfriend by Mabel
songs.title: Boyfriend

description.plain:
“Boyfriend” is an upbeat self-love anthem that warns girls to not lose their value when searching for a significant other. Mabel sings about wanting a boyfriend that can handle her. She explained:

[I wrote this song] to remind you all that wanting someone in your life doesn’t mean you can’t still be that bitch.

The song was first teased on February 22nd, 2020. In the following days, Mabel slowly released lyric snippets alongside photos from the music video. The video clip was released simultaneously with the song. According to Mabel, it was “90s Aaliyah” inspired.

The single was retrospectively added to Mabel’s debut album High Expectations, released in August 2019.
